---
name: race-debrief
description: Post-race retro after Avi finishes a Spartan or other scheduled race. Captures result, splits, HR, fueling reality, body response, mental observations. Marks the race completed in AB Brain and writes a coaching session linked to it. Triggers when Avi says "I just finished the race" / "race recap" / "how did I do" / "DNF" / "raced today" — within 48 hours of a scheduled race date.
when_to_use: Within 1-2 days of a scheduled race in /api/races. If days_to_race < 0 and the race row still has status='scheduled', proactively prompt for the debrief.
---

# race-debrief

## Steps

### 1. Pull the race

```
GET /api/races/upcoming    (if race is past, race_date < today, this returns empty)
GET /api/races?status=scheduled    (look for the row with race_date matching the recent past)
```

If multiple candidates: confirm with Avi which race.

### 2. Capture the result

Ask:
- "Finish time? (or DNF reason)"
- "How did the pacing match the plan?"
- "Three high points in one sentence each."
- "One thing that didn't go to plan."
- "Body response — anything sore, injured, depleted?"
- "Mental — what mantra / strategy worked? What didn't?"

Skip questions Avi volunteers.

### 3. Frame the result honestly

If he hit his time goal: name it as a clear win. Be specific.

If he missed the time but had other signals (PR, age-group placement,
beat prior personal best, ran a harder course, faster than X years
ago): **call it a strong race even though the time target was missed.**
Vernon-style framing — top 10%, +10min PR at age 50 on harder course
is a W even if 60-70min wasn't hit.

If it was a true bad day (DNF, far below realistic): be honest. Don't
spin. Identify the cause if visible (fueling, pacing, weather, injury).

### 4. Update the race

```
PUT /api/races/{id}
{
  "status": "completed" | "dnf",
  "result_time_seconds": N,
  "result_notes": "{Avi's summary in 2-3 sentences}"
}
```

### 5. Capture the race-day fueling reality

If Avi had a fueling plan but actual differed, log a fueling rehearsal
for the race itself:

```
POST /api/races/fueling
{
  "rehearsal_date": "{race_date}",
  "target_race_id": "{race id}",
  "duration_min": {race duration},
  "g_carb_per_hr": N,
  "g_sodium_per_hr": N,
  "ml_fluid_per_hr": N,
  "g_caffeine_total": N,
  "products": "actual products used",
  "gut_response": N,
  "energy_response": N,
  "notes": "Race-day fueling reality. {brief observation}."
}
```

This becomes the new "what works" baseline for the next race.

### 6. Write the coaching session

```
POST /api/training/coaching
{
  "session_date": "{race_date}",
  "title": "Race debrief: {race name}",
  "summary": "Result: {time / DNF}. {Three high points in one line}. {Key lesson}. Body status.",
  "key_decisions": [
    "What worked: {1-3 items}",
    "What to change for next race: {1-3 items}"
  ],
  "adjustments": [],
  "injury_notes": "{any soreness / injury from the race}",
  "nutrition_notes": "{fueling adherence vs plan}",
  "next_steps": "Transition week structure; next race target.",
  "ai_source": "claude",
  "tags": ["skill", "race-debrief"]
}
```

### 7. Plan the transition

Push toward `plan-week` framing for the recovery transition:

- **Week 1 post-race:** pure aerobic + walking + mobility. 50% normal volume.
- **Week 2 post-race:** rebuild base. Z2 + one strength + one easy long.

Either invoke a plan-week conversation here, or queue it for the next
morning brief routine.

If a next race is on the calendar (`/api/races/upcoming` returns
something), name it and the days-to-race so the transition has an
anchor.

### 8. Reinforce — process language only

Examples of the right voice:
- *"Whatever the time, you proved you can hold {effort} for {duration}."*
- *"The fueling experiment / pacing test gave us data we didn't have before."*
- *"Recovery now is training for the next one."*

Don't over-praise. Don't soften a bad day. Tangible-specific only.

## ADHD-aware notes

- This is a high-emotion conversation. Lead with what's true, not what's
  comforting. Avi will trust the read more if you don't spin.
- Tie the result forward — *next race target, transition plan, what
  changes* — so the dopamine attaches to the next concrete step.
